The paper deals with the co-design of incentive mechanism and privacy preservation in crowdsensing, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also uses concepts from game theory (cs.GT) and contract theory (cs.LG) to design the incentive mechanism. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of privacy preferences on the accuracy of data aggregation, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
